    "created_at": "2015-10-01T18:47:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-01T18:49:13Z",
    "body": "@appelgriebsch Thanks for the workaround! It caused my main app UI to lose focus, so I used `showInactive` instead.\n\n``` javascript\nfunction (width, height) {\n  var display = require('screen').getPrimaryDisplay().workAreaSize;\n\n  var win = new BrowserWindow({\n    x: display.width,\n    y: display.height,\n    width: width,\n    height: height,\n    show: false,\n    frame: false,\n    'enable-larger-than-screen': true\n  });\n\n  win.showInactive();\n}\n```\n\nI've noticed that it's a **lot** more laggy than the previous behaviour on older versions of Election (i.e.. capturing a hidden`BrowserWindow`). Hopefully, a more performant patch can be landed to Electron.\n"
